\f0 \cf0 1.	Introduction
\f1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\qj\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs10 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\qj\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 Congratulations you are about to try an amazing 3D audio reproduction system that produces effects you probably haven\'92t dreamt of or thought possible! The plugin produces stable audio images in 3D using the Compensated Amplitude Panning (CAP) algorithm\super ,\nosupersub . This exploits 6 degree-of-freedom headtracking to provide 3D images with as few as 2 loudspeakers, removing the need for many surrounding loudspeakers to generate an immersive experience. CAP covers frequencies to ~1000 Hz. Higher frequencies are covered by an adaptive VBIP panner built into the plugin. The signal routing of CAP and VBIP in the plugin are shown below, LXa and HX are cross over filters:\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\qc\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\qj\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
 The plugin can be used with instances of the VISR Object Panner plugin to generate the input object stream. Ideally the tracking system should be non-invasive, as well as fast and accurate. Since these are currently tough criteria to meet, for development we use an HTC Vive tracker system. Python scripts are provided to integrate with this. A REAPER session with several examples is also provided, described below. The computational cost of CAP and the plugin is very low, less than VBAP.\
\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\li397\fi-397\ri0\sb240\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0
\fs32 \cf0 2.	Features\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\qj\partightenfactor0

\fs10 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\li426\fi-437\ri0\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0
\f3\fs24 \cf0 \'a5	
\f0 Produce 3D objects using only 2 loudspeakers, that are stable to head movement and rotation.\
\ls3\ilvl0
\f3 \'a5	
\f0 Reproduce multichannel formats such as 5.1 / 7.1\
\ls3\ilvl0
\f3 \'a5	
\f0 Produce 6-degree-of-freedom (6dof) augmented audio reality scenes, in which the listener can move around objects that are positioned accurately in space, for example completely around an image.\
\ls3\ilvl0
\f3 \'a5	
\f0 Create an image in front of you with 2 loudspeakers behind you.\
\ls3\ilvl0
\f3 \'a5	
\f0 Create an image directly overhead using 2 loudspeakers in front.\
\ls3\ilvl0
\f3 \'a5	
\f0 Use 2 loudspeakers with wide separation, up to 180 degrees.\
\ls3\ilvl0
\f3 \'a5	
\f0 Integrated with modified high frequency VBIP panning, which provides full bandwidth 3D in the central position between 2 loudspeakers.\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\qj\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\li397\fi-397\ri0\sb240\partightenfactor0
