\f3 \cf0 \'a5	
\f0 Edit UDP link from the tracker system to the reproduction system. The 
\b ip
\b0  and 
\b port
\b0  settings should be edited in the extension scripts to match the host for the plugin. If using separate computers, use a direct wired ethernet connection to minimise latency.\
\ls7\ilvl0
\f3 \'a5	
\f0 Calibrate using 
\b tracker_test_DM_measureArray.py
\b0  A list of possible key controls is displayed. For a 2 loudspeaker system: first arrange the tracking device so it is measuring the position of the acoustic centre of the right hand loudspeaker. By default the measurement point is 14 cm below the centre of the underside of the tracker. Depending on the shape and size of the loudspeakers, and attachments to the tracker, this offset could be adjusted to be more convenient. 14 cm works well for the Genelec 8020 loudspeaker, with the tracker with brace placed on top. Once the tracker is correctly positioned, hit the y key. A beep should be heard and some print out produced on screen. Position the tracker for the left hand loudspeaker and hit the y key again. At this point the configuration file 
\b frameMap.json
\b0  should contain the data needed to map the co-ordinate systems. By default the origin is placed 1.6 m back from the centre of the stereo pair, which coincides with the origin assumed by the REAPER session. This can be modified to match a different origin by editing the script.\
\ls7\ilvl0
\f3 \'a5	
\f0 The above process also sends OSC messages that can be used to write to an array configuration file. Run 
\b listen-osc_writeArrayConfig.py 
\b0 in the reproduction system will pick up the messages and write to an array configuration file 
\b CAPstereo.xml
\b0  For each array setup the array configuration only needs to be formed once, and not for each recalibration. It may be more convenient to use a fixed configuration file, for example with 2 m separation, and adjust the loudspeakers to match this separation based on printed output from 
\b tracker_test_DM_measureArray.py
\b0  Example config files are included in 
\b VPS/resources/CAP/config
\b0 .\
\ls7\ilvl0
\f3 \'a5	
\f0 To start reproduction, stop other scripts (hit key e to exit calibration script) and start 
\b tracker_test_DM_head.py 
\b0 Toggle the v key to view tracker data mapped to VISR co-ordinates, and toggle t to turn tracking data on/off. The plugin should receive the tracking OSC data via its host. This script tracks the position 14 cm below the tracker centre, which is close to the average head centre position of an adult when using the brace shown above. The offset can be adjusted in the script for more accuracy.\
